Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Peel and slice the @potatoes{450%g}(peeled and sliced) into 1cm wide slices. Add them to your boiling water and simmer until just tender, ~{8-12%minutes}. > TIP: The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them. Once cooked, reserve some of the potato cooking water (see ingredient list for how much you need), then carefully drain in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use scissors if you'd prefer). Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} in a #bowl{} and add the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} and half the chives. Season with salt and @ground black pepper{}, mix together. Lay the @salmon fillets{2} on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{} and spread 1 tsp of @creme fraiche{150%g} on each fillet. Top with the breadcrumbs, pressing them down to ensure they stick. Set aside.

When the potatoes are cooked and drained, pop your empty pan back on medium heat and add the remaining creme fraiche, the reserved potato water, @vegetable stock powder{1%cube}, garlic and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Stir to mix, then bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Lay the cooked potato slices in layers in an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}, then pour over the creamy mixture. Bang the dish carefully a couple of times on a hard surface to get any air bubbles out. Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and bubbly, ~{15-20%minutes}. > TIP: Put the dish on a baking tray to catch any drips.

When the potatoes have been in the oven for 5 mins, pop the salmon on the middle shelf to bake until the crumbs are golden and the salmon cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. > IMPORTANT: The salmon is cooked when opaque all the way through. While the salmon cooks, get your washing up done, then heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @purple sprouting broccoli{80%g} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{75%ml} to the pan, cover with a #lid{} or some #tin foil{} and steam fry until almost tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the broccoli is almost tender, add the @sugar snap peas{80%g} to the pan, season with salt and pepper, cover with a lid again and allow to steam until the sugar snaps are tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Remove the pan from the heat. Carefully transfer the salmon to plates and add a generous spoonful of dauphinoise potato. Finish with the purple sprouting and sugar snaps and a sprinkle of chives. Enjoy!